{"_id":"blackshadowseizure001","name":"Black Shadows from Stories","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"When Sherazade rejected the Sultan's offering, all the stories she had told over thirty nights took physical shape as black shadows. These shadows emerged from the walls to seize the Sultan and hold him in terrible darkness for eternity. This was the first manifestation of Sherazade's power to bring her stories to life as vengeful entities. The black shadows represent the dark transformation of beautiful tales into weapons of punishment. This origin story explains why her current Shadows are 'darker, sadder versions' of the originals.","location":"Manifested at the Sultan's court, now part of Sherazade's Gift","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"dinarzadssmile001","name":"Dinarzad's Smile Memory","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Sherazade has her sister Dinarzad's smile etched in her mind as the last happy moment she can recall. This memory is so powerful that not even the Sultan's great wealth could erase it. When the Sultan offered Sherazade all his riches and power to forget Dinarzad's death and become his bride, this cherished memory gave her the strength to summon all her stories as black shadows to seize the Sultan. Understanding this emotional anchor is key to reaching Sherazade's wounded soul and potentially turning her from enemy to ally.","location":"Sherazade's deepest memory, discoverable through interaction","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"shadowfocusobjects001","name":"Shadow Focus Objects","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Small objects left behind when Sherazade's Shadows dissipate after being defeated. These items are typical of the area where Sherazade currently resides - could be a coin, a garment, or a poem. By collecting these focus objects, the Hunters discover they serve as anchors to animate the Shadows and that all objects come from the same geographical area. These clues allow the Hunters to track Sherazade's location by identifying the region of Europe where she is performing her stories.","location":"Dropped by defeated Shadows, various locations","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"shadowwarnings001","name":"Shadow's Warning Words","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"When Sherazade's Shadows have an obvious advantage, they speak revealing phrases: 'My Lady Sherazade will be proud of me.' When defeated, a Shadow can exit the scene shouting 'My Lady Sherazade will avenge me.' These verbal clues confirm Sherazade's involvement and her control over the Shadows. The Shadows' loyalty and their references to 'My Lady' help Hunters understand they are facing servants of a more powerful Dark Presence rather than independent threats.","location":"Spoken by Shadows during combat encounters","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"sherazadesstorytelling001","name":"Sherazade's Storytelling Performance","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"At the end of each story when a Scenario is solved, the Hunters witness a short scene of Sherazade with her audience entranced by what has just been told. The first time, this vision allows the Hunters to understand the region of Europe where the Weaver of Tales is located. The second time, Sherazade herself turns towards them smiling, underlining the mutual awareness of the bond her story has created. This supernatural connection reveals crucial information about Sherazade's whereabouts and her awareness of the Hunters.","location":"Vision at the end of Scenarios affected by Sherazade","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"stoopedwriteralliance001","name":"Alliance with the Stooped Writer","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Empty of any emotion after her sister's death and revenge on the Sultan, Sherazade wandered all over the known world. She finally met a tired and stooped man - a writer who, like her, had seen every happy memory destroyed by the selfishness of others. The two forged a bitter alliance to bring new life into the stories now broken by the wish of the Child Savior. This alliance connects Sherazade directly to the overarching campaign narrative involving the Child Savior and The One Who Plots in the Shadows.","location":"Part of Sherazade's history, clues on page 246 of manual","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"storyentrapment001","name":"Story Entrapment Technique","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Sherazade's ability to trap the Hunters inside the stories she tells. Hunters awaken within a story she's performing, experiencing it as both audience members and participants. The story always begins with Sherazade's introduction: 'Good evening my dear hosts, my name is Sherazade and I am a weaver of tales. My words will take you to incredible worlds... however this story is not like the others and these feats are not just imaginary.' Understanding this technique allows Hunters to potentially reverse it, using magic or Order Treasures to drag Sherazade into one of her own stories.","location":"Manifests when Hunters are trapped in Sherazade's narratives","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"sultansoffering001","name":"The Sultan's Rejected Offering","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"After thirty nights of beautiful stories, the Sultan threw himself at Sherazade's feet weeping, offering her all his wealth, power, and everything she might desire to forget her sister Dinarzad and become his bride. The Sultan had executed Dinarzad the first night, certain of Sherazade's failure. This betrayal and false offering reveals the Sultan's cruel nature and Sherazade's traumatic origin. Understanding that Sherazade rejected infinite wealth for love of her sister explains her current emptiness and her bitter alliance with the stooped writer to bring new life to broken stories.","location":"Part of Sherazade's backstory, discoverable through investigation","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
